[{"id":"FT543113","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"<p>The four pictures present a story. Imagine you are writing the story to a friend. Narrate a complete story as suggested by the pictures. Give your story a beginning, a middle, and an end.</p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"Four pictures are shown in a square grid to present a story.   Picture 1 is in the upper left corner. A boy and a girl are outside on the grass. The girl is wearing a baseball glove and throwing a baseball to the boy, who is swinging a bat at the ball. Their backpacks are lying on a bench nearby and there are houses in the background.   Picture 2 is in the upper right corner. The boy is taking his backpack off the bench. The girl is grabbing his arm and pointing at a broken window on the house across the street from them.   Picture 3 is in the lower left corner. The boy and girl are wearing their backpacks and standing outside the front door of the house with the broken window. The girl is pressing the doorbell, from which music notes are coming, and the boy is looking through the window on the door.   Picture 4 is in the lower right corner. The boy and girl are standing outside the front door, and the girl is writing a note on a piece of paper pressed up against the front door of the house. The boy is holding the mailbox top open and pointing at the opening.\" height=\"299\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/302dbae3abf0b09565a350d0d133ff52/original.jpg\" width=\"300\" /></p>\n","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"You will be asked to perform two writing tasks in Chinese. In each case, you will be asked to write for a specific purpose and to a specific person. You should write in as complete and as culturally appropriate a manner as possible, taking into account the purpose and the person described.&nbsp;Type your response in the target language."}]}]